National Drug Law Enforcement Agency (NDLEA) in partnership with Christabels Initiative had sensitised Nigerians especially youths to desist from drug abuse and other vices that can endanger their future. The Convener of the group, Dr Christabel Regan Okoye, made the call yesterday during the 2020 Youth International Day celebration themed Youth Engagement for Global Action in Abuja. She said “Youths are the pinnacle of our society, the bedrock of any nation and leaders of tomorrow. “It is very important we recognise and celebrate them, especially those who have impacted lives positively, they are very distinguished and have in different ways paid a great price in making other youths proud and worthy of emulation. “No youth become relevant by living an irresponsible and nonchalant life. History has not produced any drug abused youth who made a generational impact and became a role model. She said responsible youths are visionaries and focused people who would assume responsible positions of leadership tomorrow, adding that it was in view of this, that this event was held. The representative of NDLEA at the event, Kingsley Iyamu said drug abuse was very dangerous to not only the youth but the society at large. He noted that NDLEA has establish standard rehabilitation centres that would see to the needs of drug addicts and other social misfits in the country. The NGO also award the National President of TAKOM, Dr Rachael Adewumi and Hon. Barr Pius Sunday Okeoma, for their outstanding support.